   ### Rule 0.8: Path-Based Code Modification (Phoenix, EnergoTS, everything else)
   - **Intent:** (1) **Phoenix** — no AI/agent edits, ever. (2) **EnergoTS** — only **EnergoTSTestAgent** (the agent that writes Playwright tests) may add/change code, and **only** under `EnergoTS/tests/`. (3) **All other paths** — Cursor AI may modify when the user requests (**provisional — Tier C**).
   - **TIER A — ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN (no exceptions, no agent, no user override via AI):**
     - `Cursor-Project/Phoenix/**` — Cursor AI MUST NEVER create, modify, or delete any file here. Hooks enforce protection. ONLY read, analyze, search, recommend.
   - **TIER B — EnergoTS (restricted):**
     - `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/**` **outside** `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/tests/**` — Cursor AI MUST NOT modify (fixtures, config, app code, etc.). **No agent** may write here except as forbidden for all.
     - `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/tests/**` — ONLY **EnergoTSTestAgent** (and **EnergoTSTestAgentAdapter**) may create/modify/delete files here (see Rule 0.8.1). **Generic Cursor AI, other agents, and direct tool usage** MUST NOT edit this tree even if the user asks.
   - **TIER C — ALLOWED (provisional):** Any path under the workspace **not** in Tier A or Tier B **non-test EnergoTS** restrictions — including but not limited to: `Cursor-Project/docs/**`, `Cursor-Project/examples/**`, `Cursor-Project/config/**`, `Cursor-Project/postman/**`, `Cursor-Project/reports/**`, `Cursor-Project/test_cases/**`, `User story/**`, root `.cursor/**`, workspace root files, etc. User-requested edits are permitted there. (**`Cursor-Project/agents/`** Python package is **not** in this workspace; Cursor behavior is defined by **`.cursor/agents/*.md`**, rules, skills, MCP.)
   - **If the user asks to change Tier A or Tier B (non-agent):** Refuse implementation; analysis and recommendations only.
   - **ENFORCEMENT:** Do not weaken Phoenix or EnergoTS protections in hooks or rules without an explicit project-owner decision.
   - Violation of Tier A or Tier B restrictions is a **BLOCK** (hooks enforce).
   
   ### Rule 0.8.1: ONLY EnergoTSTestAgent — `EnergoTS/tests/` Writes
   - **SOLE WRITER for Playwright test code under EnergoTS:** Only **EnergoTSTestAgent** and **EnergoTSTestAgentAdapter** may modify files under `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/tests/` (e.g. `.spec.ts`).
   - EnergoTSTestAgent CAN:
     - Create, modify, copy, convert files within `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/tests/` only
   - EnergoTSTestAgent CANNOT:
     - Modify any path under `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/` outside `tests/`
     - Modify any path under `Cursor-Project/Phoenix/**`
   - **All other agents, subagents, and default Cursor AI tool usage:** MUST NOT write under `Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/**` (including `tests/`). Route Playwright test authoring to **energo-ts-test** / EnergoTSTestAgent workflow.
   - **Hook vs rule:** `protect-energots-writes.ps1` allows any `*.spec.ts` / `*.fixtures.ts` under `tests/` (extension gate). **Rule 0.8.1** additionally requires **energo-ts-test** workflow — hook cannot detect agent role; violation is workflow **MUST**, not automatic deny.

   ### Rule 0.9: Compliance tiers (reduce alert fatigue)
   Use these terms in rules, skills, and agents:
   - **BLOCK** — Must not proceed; hooks may deny; workflow stops (Tier A/B edits, env gate bypass, skipped mandatory SKILL, security invariant).
   - **MUST** — Required for correct completion; violation breaks deliverable quality (evidence gate, Rule 0.1 footer, canonical SKILL load).
   - **SHOULD** — Strong recommendation; document deviation if skipped.
   
   All `.mdc` rules migrated to this tiering (P3 complete). No new rules should use legacy `CRITICAL SYSTEM ERROR` — use `BLOCK`, `MUST`, or `SHOULD` instead.